Ed,<br><br>
I think about the wisdom of your ancestors.  The values of life which they passed on to their children.<br><br>
I studies these things once when I lived in Nebraska.  I have written papers on the Indian wars.<br><br>
The native American, especially the plains tribes,  connected their warriors with the elements of nature and the animals that roamed the earth.  Everything has it's place and respect.  No man has ever accomplished this better.<br><br>
I will reflect on these things.  I would like to have a thread where you can those those who seek the answer of the inner peace your grandfather knew.  You possess the wisdom of a chief.  I would be like to learn these ways and understand what we may have lost along the way.<br><br>
Your Brother of Choice
